# Cache headers configuration
# 
# NOTE: GitHub Pages does not support custom _headers files.
# GitHub Pages automatically applies the following default headers:
# - Cache-Control: max-age=600 (10 minutes) for HTML files
# - Cache-Control: max-age=3600 (1 hour) for static assets
# - Automatic gzip compression for text-based files
# - Security headers (X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
#
# This file is kept for documentation purposes and for potential
# migration to other hosting platforms (Netlify, Cloudflare Pages, etc.)
# that support custom headers.
#
# Recommended headers for optimal performance:

# Cache static assets for 1 year (immutable content)
/styles.min.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  
/app.min.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/projects.json
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate

# Cache HTML for 1 hour with revalidation
/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate

# Security and compression headers
/*
  Content-Encoding: gzip
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
